%p After seeing the <a href="http://www.fenixoutfitters.com/amsler-knives-hurricane-razor-without-tritium-627">Amsler Hurricane Razor</a> a few weeks ago, I was inspired by the idea of a small exacto/scalpel type knife as an EDC alternative. I decided to have a go at my own interpretation of the idea.

%p In general I do not like hollow grinds, so I decided once again to go for a full flat grind. The knife was made from 5/32" (4mm) O1 tool steel. It was sandblasted and waxed, then fitted with a tiny kydex sheath.

